		<p>At 19, I moved to Germany to study mathematics at the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_University_of_Berlin" target="blank">Free University of Berlin</a>.<br>Over there, I fell in love with <a href="http://techcrunch.com/tag/berlin/" target="blank">Berlin's vibrant startup scene</a>. Seeing so many people risk everything to build companies they were passionate about was unbelievable.</p>
		<p>So I chose to end school early and focus on what I think is awesome: mobile tech.<br>In the next few years I will be building software and hardware that will appear everywhere we go. Technologies that will improve <a href="http://www.wsj.com/articles/the-future-of-medicine-is-in-your-smartphone-1420828632" target="blank">health</a>, education, and unemployment problems all around the world.</p>

